  <static seed="108" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberSubtractionWordProblems40.pg">
    <statement><p>When driving on a high way,  noticed a sign saying exit to Johnstown is <m>2{{\frac{3}{4}}}</m> miles away, while exit to Jerrystown is <m>4{{\frac{1}{4}}}</m> miles away. How far is Johnstown from Jerrystown?</p>
<p>Johnstown and Jerrystown are <fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/> miles apart.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the distance between Johnstown and Jerrystown, we need to find the difference between their distance. This implies subtraction. We could treat subtraction as <lq/>adding a negative<rq/>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
   4{{\frac{1}{4}}} -2{{\frac{3}{4}}}
      \amp = 4{{\frac{1}{4}}} + (-2{{\frac{3}{4}}}) \\
      \amp = 4 + {{\frac{1}{4}}} + (-2) + (-{{\frac{3}{4}}}) \\
      \amp = 4 + (-2) + {{\frac{1}{4}}} + (-{{\frac{3}{4}}}) \\
      
      \amp = 2 + \frac{1}{4} + (-\frac{3}{4}) \\
      \amp = 2 + \frac{1+(-3)}{4} \\
      \amp = 2 + (-\frac{2}{4}) \\
      \amp = 2 + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}})
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>From here, there are two methods to continue.</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to make this a level 2 header. -->
<p>
Method 1</p>
<p>We can <lq/>split<rq/> <m>1</m> from the integer, and do <m>1 + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}})</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
      \amp {\phantom{{}=}} 2 + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = 1 + 1 + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = 1 + \frac{2}{2} + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = 1 + \frac{2-1}{2} \\
      \amp = 1 + \frac{1}{2} \\
      \amp = {1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Note that we changed <m>1</m> to <m>\frac{2}{2}</m>.</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to make this a level 2 header. -->
<p>
Method2</p>
<p>We could simply change the whole number <m>2</m> into a fraction without <lq/>splitting<rq/> <m>1</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
      \amp {\phantom{{}=}} 2 + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = \frac{2}{1} + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = \frac{2\cdot2}{1\cdot2} + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = \frac{4}{2} + ({-{\frac{1}{2}}}) \\
      \amp = \frac{4+(-1)}{2} \\
      \amp = \frac{3}{2} \\
      \amp = {1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>ran <m>{1{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> more miles than .</p>
</solution>
